== Shares as an Investment

#info[*Investment Ratio*\

$ "Price/Earning Ratio" = frac("Market price per share of Common Stock", "Earnings per share") $

$ "Dividend Yield" = frac("Divided per share of Common Stock",  "Market price per share of Common Stock") $

The higher these two ratios are, the better the investment is.

$ "Book Value" = frac("Total Shareholders' Equity" - "Preferred Equity", "Weighted-average number of Common shares Outstanding") $

]

